<br>
Yes, we have a serious problem with the two big asian guilds, especially eastern keep.  These 2 guilds used to be allianced, but something happened a couple of weeks ago, causing them to sever ties.  EK, is a weak guild that can no longer do certain things, and literally rides on the backs of others to accomplish things now.  Not to mention their leader is the most server wide hated person I have ever encountered.  However; there are some new alliances amongst some higher level guilds that can do stuff.  A perfect example is my guild Dol Amroth, and their alliance guild Echoes in Eternity.  I won't get into the whole NToV thing w/ you guys.  I like cass and eel a lot.  I respect what they say, and have positive feelings towards them in general.  I was really happy when they went out of their way to tell me grats when i hit 60.  I wasn't at ToV on Wednesday when the shizznat hit the fan.  I was at NToV for about 30 minutes, but w/ 180 peeps in the zone, and going LD 4 times in 20 minutes, decided it wasn't worth the hassle.  And I don't think you are meaning to mention da/eie when you  say some guilds are doing stuff on your coat tails.  We won't go into it. <br>
<br>
But this does lead to the problem that most people have hit on.....we don't need any more 1-50 zones.  Maybe a couple of dungeons for the 30-50 crowd would be cool, on the par w/ lower guk and sol b.  But seriously, even today, the dreadlands is the zone to be in for outdoor 40ish grind.  We dont need more.  What we do need is more Raid oriented and even single group oriented 50+ dungeons.<br>
I may miss some, so bear w/ me. <br>
 Here are the single group dungeons 50+ (not including SoL, i don't go there often to know)<br>
Sebilis<br>
Howling Stones<br>
Chardok<br>
Velks<br>
Sirens Grotto<br>
Karnor's Castle....i guess<br>
opening areas of Icewell Keep<br>
<br>
Here are the 50+ raid zones (including the sol ones i know of)<br>
Western Wastes<br>
Temple of Veeshan<br>
Veeshan's Peak (if you are patient enough to do this inane quest)<br>
Akheva (also has some decent single group grinds)<br>
Juggs/Trak<br>
Ssra Temple<br>
RoF<br>
Planes: Fear, Hate, Growth, Mischief (if even anyone goes here), Air (epic stuff only)<br>
<br>
I'm sure I am missing some, but the point is this......Our server has about 7-8 guilds/alliances capable of doing most if not all of this stuff.  That doesn't seem like a lot of guilds, BUT, almost all of this stuff is on a 3 day timer.  On RN, most of the 3+day timer stuff drops w/ in 12 hours of a patch.  Then, we all wait for 3+ more days to do it again.  There is not enough to go around.  Hence, especially in the last 2 days, there has been some serious strife going on between the higher guilds.  Da/eie have recently made some serious upgrades to their killing ability.  Took us about a month of working together, but we have now done Yelinak, the NToV mobs that have been up we have done.  We've come a long way in the past 2 months, and are ready for out next challenge.  The monopoly held by AoD and Ascent is quickly ending.  And a lot of other guilds are gearing for NToV, when in the past it was just those 2 guilds.  What is the solution? I wish I knew.  I don't want to start guild wars which will end, although very casual, friends I have made in several guilds.  Probably one of the best solutions would be to decrease the spawn time of the mobs, and make their drop stuff slightly more rare.  That probably won't help either.  <br>
<br>
There needs to be something though, or enough people will say the hell with this, this is a game, I dont need to be more stressed playing EQ than I do in my real life career.  Cass and Eel, you guys are great, screw EK, and we'll all figure something out <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
