<br>
A good guild can rip through NToV in 6-8 hours, getting about 40 very great drops.  Compare to Luclin, where there's like one boss mob in every zone.  Since CoH is disabled in pretty much every Luclin raid zone (Ssra, Greigs, Acrylia, The Deep, etc.), you gotta fight through the entire dungeon, taking a good 2-3 hours per raid target... and the popular one (THO) doesn't even respawn upon server resets, and smaller Asian guilds almost always get the Rhags in Ssra, and sometimes accidentally spawn the Glyphed.  Again, you can't rake in the loot ANYWHERE nearly as fast as you can in NToV.<br>
<br>
VP was THE uber raid zone when Velious was released.  It was quickly abandoned as people started killing the earlier boss mobs in Velious, whom dropped far superior loot to VP, and there were a lot more better loot obvious just over the horizon.  This all let up to NToV.  But now that Luclin was released... NToV is STILL the best raid zone available, bar none.  And it *will* continue to be top priority for every guild until Vex Thal is finally released... assuming Vex Thal is similar to NToV.  If it's not, then NToV will STILL probably be the prime target.<br>
<br>
NToV used to be a LOT harder.  Things got a lot easier during that DAoC release patch, where they upgraded melee damage, and reduced resistances.  They rescaled the mobs a bit, but it wasn't enough.  I can say from experience that things got significantly easier that day.  Then when you factor in AA skills, where wizards will do double damage every 6 casts, tanks have 10% more HP, tanks take less damage, casters and priests regen mana faster, priests heal better, spells become more mana efficient, etc.  Things just get easier and easier.<br>
<br>
It's simply a problem that Verant needs to address.  Unfortunately, I think they're over their heads here, and the only way to fix the NToV problem is to create a new NToV raid zone... and then probably yet another a few months after that.  The presence of NToV has severely altered the high-end game recently, no question about it.<br>
<br>
EDIT: To make matters worse, Verant is bloating the loot tables of the new Luclin mobs with, how shall I put it... crap.  Yes, most mobs have a VERY nice drop or two mixed in with a couple average drops.  But lately, Verant has added a ton of cleric weapons that proc DDs, shaman weapons that proc DDs, druid weapons that proc DDs, wizard weapons that proc DDs, mage weapons that proc DDs, necro weapons that proc DDs... and these weapons have stats inferior to epics, let alone the stuff from NToV.  Why they're watering down the good drops like this, I dunno.  I would think that at this point, they'd want to do all they could to encourage players to move away from NToV... <p><a href="http://www.reconstructed.nu/profile.php?pid=119">Baron Aledar Boomcaster</a><br>Sorcerer of <a href="http://www.reconstructed.nu/">Reconstructed</a>, E'ci<br><img src="http://www.seas.upenn.edu/~bwa/kerasig.jpg"></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ualedar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aledar</A> at: 2/1/02 9:22:34 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukrusch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krusch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/1/02 9:04:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12240.topic&index=62>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Solution</span><hr size=1> They can always do a complete player wipe. If nothing else it would weed out all the crybabies.<br>
